solutions.content:
We use two heap:
1. one is for free servers  ( keep track of servers available )
2.  one is for busy servers (  keep track of the tasks that are still in progress )

Here, we have two min heaps, ordered by [weight, index, time].
First, we put all servers into the available heap with time equals to zero.


As we process our tasks:
1.  Move servers that have finished (time <= t) from busyServers to freeServers.
2.  If no servers are available.   
	* We use the top server from busyServers.
4.   ELSE
       * Pick the top server from the avail heap and move it to the busy heap with time = t + tasks[t].

O((M + N) * logN)
```
import java.util.Comparator;
import java.util.PriorityQueue;

class Solution {

    public int[] assignTasks(int[] servers, int[] tasks) {
        PriorityQueue<int[]> freeServers = new PriorityQueue<>(new Comparator<int[]>() {
            @Override
            public int compare(int[] o1, int[] o2) {
                //o1[0] and o2[0] is 'weight' of servers
                //o1[1] and o2[1] is 'index' of servers
                //o1[2] and o2[2] is 'busy till' of servers
                //Free server heap is sorted based on weight and index.
                return o1[0] != o2[0] ? o1[0] - o2[0] : o1[1] - o2[1];
            }
        });
        PriorityQueue<int[]> busyServers = new PriorityQueue<>(new Comparator<int[]>() {
            @Override
            public int compare(int[] o1, int[] o2) {
                //busy server heap is sorted on available time.
                return o1[2] != o2[2] ? o1[2] - o2[2] : (o1[0] != o2[0] ? o1[0] - o2[0] : o1[1] - o2[1]);
            }
        });
		// Initially Push all servers in freeServer Min Heap
        for (int i = 0; i < servers.length; i++) {
            freeServers.add(new int[]{servers[i], i, 0});
        }
        int[] result = new int[tasks.length];
        for (int i = 0; i < tasks.length; i++) {
            int task = tasks[i];
            while (!busyServers.isEmpty() && busyServers.peek()[2] <= i) {
                freeServers.add(busyServers.poll());
            }
			//check at this point if at this time instance any servers are freed or not from used server
            if (freeServers.isEmpty()) {
                int[] cur = busyServers.poll();
                result[i] = cur[1];
                cur[2] += task;
                busyServers.add(cur);
            } else {
                int[] cur = freeServers.poll();
                result[i] = cur[1];
                cur[2] = i + task;
                busyServers.add(cur);
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}
