# Simulation
## Intuition
At any task arriving at time t between 0 and m-1, we should:
1. Release all busy servers which finish tasks before <= t
2. If still no free servers, we have to release the earliest avaiable busy server
3. Pick the free server with minimum weight and index to work on the task.

## Algorithm
1. Create a PriorityQueue for free servers, ordered by weight then index, add all servers 
2. Create a TreeMap for busy servers, with key as next available time and value as a list of servers
3. For t = 0 to m-1:
3.1 Release all busy servers with available time <= t and add to free servers
3.2 If still no free servers, release the earliest available busy server
3.3 Poll one free server and assign to the task t

Time: O(nlogn + mlogn), as free servers and busy servers add up to n, and in the worst case either free or busy servers can be up to n.
Space: O(n)

```java
class Solution {
    public int[] assignTasks(int[] servers, int[] tasks) {
        // Free servers [{index, weight}]
        PriorityQueue<int[]> freeServers = 
            new PriorityQueue<>((a, b) -> a[1] != b[1] ? a[1] - b[1] : a[0] - b[0]);
        for (int i = 0; i < servers.length; i++) {
            freeServers.offer(new int[]{i, servers[i]});
        }

        TreeMap<Integer, List<int[]>> busyServers = new TreeMap<>(); // Busy servers (availableTime -> [{index, weight}])
        int[] assigned = new int[tasks.length]; // server index tasks assigned with
        int freeTime = 0; // next free server's available time

        for (int t = 0; t < tasks.length; t++) {
            freeTime = Math.max(freeTime, t); // lower bound freeTime to "now"

            // release busy servers finishing before t
            while (!busyServers.isEmpty() && busyServers.firstKey() <= freeTime) {
                freeServers.addAll(busyServers.pollFirstEntry().getValue());
            }

            // If free servers still empty, release earliest available busy servers
            if (freeServers.isEmpty()) {
                freeTime = busyServers.firstKey();
                freeServers.addAll(busyServers.pollFirstEntry().getValue());
            }

            // Poll a free server and assign to current task
            int[] server = freeServers.poll();
            assigned[t] = server[0];
            busyServers.computeIfAbsent(freeTime + tasks[t], ignored -> new ArrayList<>()).add(server);
        }
        return assigned;
    }
}
```
# Simulation 2
A slightly more intuitive simulation approach is to keep a freeTasks queue, and sweeps one single time line.
## Algorithm
1. Create a PriorityQueue for free servers, ordered by weight then index, add all servers 
2. Create a TreeMap for busy servers, with key as next available time and value as a list of servers, and a queue for free tasks.
3. For t = 0 to m-1, or when freeTasks is non-empty:
3.1 Add a free task t if t < m
3.2 Release all busy servers with available time <= t and add to free servers
3.3 While freeServers and freeTasks are both non-empty, poll one free server and one free task to match
3.4 Update next t to t+1 if t < m, otherwise use next busy server availableTime.

The time and space complexity remain the same as we only poll m freeServers in total.

```java
class Solution {
    public int[] assignTasks(int[] servers, int[] tasks) {
        // Free servers [{index, weight}]
        PriorityQueue<int[]> freeServers = 
            new PriorityQueue<>((a, b) -> a[1] != b[1] ? a[1] - b[1] : a[0] - b[0]);
        for (int i = 0; i < servers.length; i++) {
            freeServers.offer(new int[]{i, servers[i]});
        }

        TreeMap<Integer, List<int[]>> busyServers = new TreeMap<>(); // Busy servers (availableTime -> [{index, weight}])
        Queue<Integer> freeTasks = new LinkedList<>();
        int[] assigned = new int[tasks.length]; // server index tasks assigned with

        for (int t = 0; t < tasks.length || !freeTasks.isEmpty();) {
            if (t < tasks.length) {
                freeTasks.offer(t);
            }

            // release busy servers finishing before t
            while (!busyServers.isEmpty() && busyServers.firstKey() <= t) {
                freeServers.addAll(busyServers.pollFirstEntry().getValue());
            }

            // Poll free servers and assign to current freeTasks
            while (!freeServers.isEmpty() && !freeTasks.isEmpty()) {
                int[] server = freeServers.poll();
                int task = freeTasks.poll();
                assigned[task] = server[0];
                busyServers.computeIfAbsent(t + tasks[task], ignored -> new ArrayList<>()).add(server);
            }

            // Next time to check
            if (t < tasks.length) {
                t++;
            } else {
                t = busyServers.firstKey(); // busyServers should be non-empty until all tasks finished
            }
        }
        return assigned;
    }
}
```

